                  <additions>

                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <desc>
                          <locus target="#127r" facs="129"> f. 127r, top</locus>: Excerpt of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse Māryām</title> for Monday.
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                          <desc>
                            <locus target="#127r" facs="129"> f. 127r bottom</locus>: Excerpt of <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2835RepCh119">Malkǝʾa Mikāʾel</title>
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                          <desc>
                          <locus target="#127v #128r" facs="130"/> One Miracle of Michael, Tä’ammǝrä Mika’el, How God gave wealth to a certain man who had honored the feast day of Saint Michael though his farm had been destroyed by a devouring worm.
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                          <desc>
                          <locus target="#128r" facs="130"> f. 128r col. 2</locus>: Instructions for prayer and anointing in time of dispute and for protection when the enemy comes.
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                          <desc>
                          The manuscript contains the following marginalia:
                            <locus target="#95v" facs="098"> f. 95v top margin</locus>: Note about canticle two, the Prayer of Moses
                            <locus target="#95v" facs="098"> f. 95v, top margin</locus>: Note about canticle two, the Prayer of Moses.
                            <locus target="#99r" facs="101"> f. 99r, top margin</locus>: Note about canticle six, the Prayer of Manasseh.
                            <locus target="#103r" facs="105"> f. 103r, top margin</locus>: Note about canticle twelve, the Prayer of Isaiah.
                            <locus from="105v" to="106v" facs="108"> f. 105v, top margin</locus>: Note on the meaning of the Song of Songs.
                            <locus from="112r" to="113v" facs="114"/>: marginal notation.
                            <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/>, <locus from="132v" to="133v" facs="135"/>: Scrawls.
                            </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <desc>
                        Scribal intervention:
                        words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#9r #65v #77r #92v #106r" facs="011 068 079 095 108"/> etc.);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#105v" facs="108"/>);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (I) marking the location where the text is to be inserted<locus target="#20v" facs="023"> f. 20v, line 2</locus>);
                        erasure markings are visible <locus target="#106r #121" facs="108 123"/>).
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate
                        script size. But #where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                      </desc>
                    </item>

                        </list>
                  </additions>
